{"parse":{"title":"Rethinking Multiculturalism: Cultural Diversity and Political Theory","pageid":57230890,"revid":852199108,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption style=\"font-style:italic;padding-bottom:0.2em;\">Rethinking Multiculturalism: Cultural Diversity and Political Theory <span class=\"Z3988\" title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Rethinking+Multiculturalism%3A+Cultural+Diversity+and+Political+Theory&amp;rft.author=Bhikhu+Parekh&amp;rft.pub=Harvard+University+Press+%28October+30%2C+2002%29\"></span></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;display:none\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\nBhikhu Parekh</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Language</th><td>\nEnglish</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Genre</th><td>\nPolitics</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Publisher</th><td>\nHarvard University Press (October 30, 2002)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0674009959\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0674009959\">0674009959</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Year_of_Multiculturalism_in_Azerbaijan.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/22/Year_of_Multiculturalism_in_Azerbaijan.jpg/220px-Year_of_Multiculturalism_in_Azerbaijan.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"226\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/22/Year_of_Multiculturalism_in_Azerbaijan.jpg/330px-Year_of_Multiculturalism_in_Azerbaijan.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/22/Year_of_Multiculturalism_in_Azerbaijan.jpg/440px-Year_of_Multiculturalism_in_Azerbaijan.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1219\" data-file-height=\"1250\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Year_of_Multiculturalism_in_Azerbaijan.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Year of Multiculturalism in Azerbaijan</div></div></div>\n<p><i><b>Rethinking Multiculturalism: Cultural Diversity and Political Theory</b></i>  is a 2000 non-fiction book by the British political theorist <a href=\"/wiki/Bhikhu_Parekh\" title=\"Bhikhu Parekh\">Bhikhu Parekh</a> and published by <a href=\"/wiki/Harvard_University_Press\" title=\"Harvard University Press\">Harvard University Press</a>. It creates and defines <a href=\"/wiki/Multiculturalism\" title=\"Multiculturalism\">multiculturalism</a> in the form of political theory as well as political practice in the modern era, being based on Parekh's experience of Multiculturalism in British society as well as other areas around the world. Parekh's book addresses several topics, primarily multicultural politics, as well as the practice and theory behind addressing these politics.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Author\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Author</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Synopsis\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Synopsis</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Reception\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Reception</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Criticism\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Criticism</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Author\">Author</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Rethinking_Multiculturalism:_Cultural_Diversity_and_Political_Theory&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Author\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Bhikhu_Parekh\" title=\"Bhikhu Parekh\">Bhikhu Parekh</a> is a political theorist who received his PHD at the <a href=\"/wiki/London_School_of_Economics\" title=\"London School of Economics\">London School of economics</a>. He has taught at University of Glasgow, University of Hull, as well as the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Westminster\" title=\"University of Westminster\">University of Westminster</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:1_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:1-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Parekh has hands on experience with multiculturalism, as he participated in several issues of multiculturalism in the UK, with a notable position as Chairman on the Commission on the Future of Multi-Ethnic Britain.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:1_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:1-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> A large amount of debate in the UK on multiculturalism stems from Parekh\u2019s work in the early 2000s on while he was Chairman. Charles Taylor addresses that Parekh\u2019s experiences gives him a stronger sense of possible situations and problems in a modern atmosphere.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Synopsis\">Synopsis</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Rethinking_Multiculturalism:_Cultural_Diversity_and_Political_Theory&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Synopsis\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Culture is the belief or view human beings create regarding the significance of human life, and in close proximity different views and sets of beliefs are created.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> In the text, Parekh approaches cultural diversity as a value, not a fact in Britain\u2019s diverse environment. Parekh writes about the dangers of avoiding ignoring diversity as well as if diversity is over addressed. analysis of culture, Montesquieu, Vico, and Herder.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:3_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:3-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> In this analysis, other theorists approach culture in a sense that is too contained, as Parekh believes culture changes on a larger scale.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:02_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:02-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> It is believed Parekh is influenced by Charles Taylor\u2019s essay on multiculturalism.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:02_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:02-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Much like Taylor, Parekh focuses avoiding ignoring several aspects of multicultural values including but not limited to education, separation and gender values.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:02_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:02-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Parekh criticizes theorists who over invest in a eurocentric view, and success relies on an equal distribution of political and economic power rather than a minority and majority.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:2_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:2-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> Parekh explores <a href=\"/wiki/Liberalism\" title=\"Liberalism\">liberalism</a> as a paradox unique to western political philosophy.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:2_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:2-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> The existence of only one way to live a good live leads to segregation of individuals in a multicultural society. Individuals who carry their own culture disturb relationships of power that in return culture has previously been established In.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:3_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:3-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> In later chapters Parekh also addresses separation of church and state will never entirely justify the separation of religion and politics, as religion represents so many citizens of most countries and in the world as a whole.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Reception\">Reception</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Rethinking_Multiculturalism:_Cultural_Diversity_and_Political_Theory&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Reception\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><i>Rethinking Multiculturalism: Cultural Diversity and Political Theory</i> has been reviewed by several political and cultural authors. While some criticism was addressed, the overall reception of Parekh\u2019s work\u2019s is positive as he attempted to remain unbiased and neutral when writing about multiculturalism. Dortha Kolodziejczyk overall acclaims it to be insightful for addressing typically unthought of issues, accrediting it to Parekh\u2019s way of thoroughly addressing both sides of the issues.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:02_5-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:02-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Criticism\">Criticism</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Rethinking_Multiculturalism:_Cultural_Diversity_and_Political_Theory&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Criticism\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Parekh's text was criticized from other cultural authors based on his opinions in the book. Many accused the text of having no real world use, and only theory to back it up.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:3_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:3-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> The text has few supported conclusions supported by real life scenarios. Other disagreement stems from Parekh's inability to address concepts of democracy, liberalism, citizenship and nation being from anywhere other than western politics.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:3_4-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:3-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> One cultural author Dortha Kolodziejczyk commented on Parekh\u2019s obsession of maintaining a non western approach to liberalism and culture while cementing liberalism as western. Kolodziejcyk says that many of Parekh\u2019s ideas do attempt to bring new ideas and perspectives, but not all of them in practice will work the way he intends.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:02_5-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:02-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Rethinking_Multiculturalism:_Cultural_Diversity_and_Political_Theory&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-:0-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-:0_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://culturemachine.net/index.php/cm/article/viewArticle/228/209\">\"Rethinking Multiculturalism: Cultural Diversity and Political Theory (2000) by Bhikhu Parekh\"</a>. <i>Culture Machine</i>. <b>1</b> (0). 2001-01-01. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Serial_Number